%N A397115 Size of clusters of star triples of Family A in the Spectre aperiodic monotile tiling.
%C A397115 The chiral aperiodic Spectre monotile tiling (discovered in 2023) forms hierarchical, fractal macro-structures called clusters of star triples (three Spectre tiles head-on) of five different families, megastars of two types, and palindromes of megastars. This sequence represents the total number of star triples in successive generations of Family A clusters. The fractal growth is governed by the limiting constant 5.674473356937..., which is the largest root of the cubic equation x^3 - 3x^2 - 15x - 1 = 0.
%H A397115 Boris K. Horvat, <a href="/A397115/b397115.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..100</a>
%H A397115 Boris K. Horvat, <a href="https://zenodo.org/records/18421797">Anatomy of the Spectre Tiling</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%H A397115 David Smith, J. S. Myers, C. S. Kaplan, and C. Goodman-Strauss, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.17743">A chiral aperiodic monotile</a>, arXiv:2305.17743 [math.CO], 2023.
%H A397115 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (4,12,-14,-1).
%F A397115 a(n) = 3*a(n-1)+15*a(n-2)+1*a(n-3)+6 (for n>2, where a(0)=0, a(1)=1, a(2)=8).
%F A397115 G.f.: x*(1 + 4*x + x^2)/((1 - x)*(1 - 3*x - 15*x^2 - x^3)). - _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 19 2026
%e A397115 For n = 2, the cluster of Family A has a(2) = 8 star triples. It is formed by the previous generation's cluster a(1) = 1 and is inflated/extended by one Type C megastar of size MC(2) = 7, giving 1 + 7 = 8 star triples.
%e A397115 For n = 3, the cluster of Family A has a(3) = 45 star triples, formed by the cluster a(2) = 8 and extended by one Type C megastar of size MC(3) = 37 (8 + 37 = 45).
%Y A397115 Cf. A397116 (Family C), A397117 (Family B), A397118 (Family D), A397119 (Family E), A397120 (Megastar A), A397121 (Megastar C), A397122 (Palindromes), A397123 (Growth constant).
